metadata.name: Updraft #23
metadata.description:
UPDRAFT seeks to reproduce the beauty of tornadoes and other vortices in a minimalist style and simple shapes, thus highlighting the purity of the lines of these fascinating objects.

If the tornado of life scares you, remember that while you will probably be a little shaken and confused on your journey, you will end up at the top of it. That's the beauty of the updraft.

[S] or [Double-Tap] when viewing in full screen to save a 4000x4000 PNG image

Artist: Estienne
August 2022
Made with p5.js
Best viewed on Chrome or Chromium-based browsers

metadata.name: Quintessence #128
metadata.description:
"Quintessence is a form of dark energy, more precisely a scalar field, postulated as an explanation of the observation of an accelerating rate of expansion of the universe. Dark and dynamic energy, the fifth and fundamental element of the universe." This artwork is inspired by this concept and tries to show a conflict between dark energy and matter that shapes the world around us. 

A heterogeneous and harmonious tension that sporadically creates a sense of transformation and conflict. Various Color Palettes and dimensions have been used.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

Made with P5js.

metadata.name: Origin Undecided #24
metadata.description:
These feel like communications from an unknown place.

Ultimately, this is a deeper exploration of familiar concepts. The code generates patterns for a couple million lines, each with extremely low opacity. As they're drawn and overlap, the color accumulates and shapes begin to form.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Chord Unknown #424
metadata.description:
The feeling of experimenting with an instrument you have not learned, and then suddenly striking an actual chord.

The code creates several grids and then applies one of six unique deformation techniques with varying intensity. It's a defined process of experimentation, and even though I'm the one that wrote the rules, each output breaks through somehow as a complete surprise to me. So when I see them, I get a Chord Unknown.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: color combinations #21
metadata.description:
the 'color combinations' series was developed as an exercise of combining colors from a single defined palette and the attempt to make all 15 selected colors being able to work within each other.

the constant pursuit for perfectionism made me design more than 200 tentatives of creating a perfect circle, and therefore the circle is the rarest output for the series.

i hope this series serves as a reference and inspire everyone out there.

2,340 possible combinations.
the closer the shape to the circle the rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%.
the bigger the shape the rarer - ranging from 30% to 20%.
beige and black colors are rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%

metadata.name: Duet #125
metadata.description:
by Daeinc
Aug 2022

Duet explores generative+computational motion and creates an almost infinite sequence of visual compositions. Two groups of shapes transform, merge, and split randomly. What can be disorienting starts to make sense as every element is animated from one to the other. This transition animation is what connects random pieces and creates a relationship between them. Each element is mathematically interpolated, with its motion defined by an equation. 

Although there are key moments, it is hard to summarize time-based work as a static image. As a constantly evolving generative motion piece, Duet invites viewers to form their impression by feeling the rhythm over time.

## Guide:
- The animation responds to window aspect ratio. It reproduces the same outcome at the same ratio. 
- For reliable playback, keep the window active and use IPFS view.
- See browser console for more info.
- Tested on MacOS 12.5.1 with Chromium 104.0

## Keyboard Interaction
- [n] to play a new random loop.
- [spacebar] to play/pause.
- [s] to save PNG. use URL params for dimensions.
- [up] and [down] to change shape resolution.
- [left] and [right] to change BPM. only works while looping. 
- [h] to toggle high DPI mode. off by default.
- [p] to toggle pixel snapping. off by default.

## URL Parameters
- add parameters separated by ampersand to the URL ex. https://.../?fxhash=...&w=1200&h=600
- [w] and [h]: set width and height in pixels. (ex. w=1200&h=600)
- [s] and [e]: set starting and ending keyframes (inclusive) for loop. (ex. s=20&e=24) 
- setting large values for start/end is not advised.
- [len]: instead of start/end, set a loop length between 1 and 16. (ex. len=4)
- [bpm]: beats per minute. (ex. bpm=80)
- [res]: shape resolution between 0 and 18. (ex. res=2)
- [pr]: pixel ratio. set it to 2 (or press [h]) for hi-DPI screens.
- [ar]: maximum aspect ratio. set to any value over 1. 1.2 by default.
- [snap]: add the param to snap to pixel grid.

## License
CC BY-NC 4.0
Please refer to the included LICENSE.md for license information.
Libraries used: canvas-sketch, canvas-sketch-util, dom-events, hsv2rgb, keyframes, equations from easings.net, array shuffle from stackoverflow.

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #1073
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: Morixels Colab #5 Gango #17
metadata.description:
The Gango collection was created from famous western symbols so that the whole world knows it.
In this collection, you can see a combination of unrelated but beautiful components.

Try your luck to have a more beautiful combination

The Gango is unique random Generated 200 PFP NFTs. The number of Traits in this collection is 9 (72 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 74,027,520 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of most Morixels Mans to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

You can read more information on Morixels website 👇

Website: https://morixels.com/

Twitter: @Morixels

by: @morteza_yousefy & @mahdirezafathi

Made in 2022

metadata.name: Redundancy #216
metadata.description:
This generative token explores redundancy as an architectural concept, method, and process. Redundancy provides flexibility in an open form, enabling a shift from monofunctional to multifunctional as well as from optimized to resilient. A hybrid architecture in which complexity is created through the continuous reconfiguration of simple discrete and compatible blocks.
Each minted redundancy token reveals various deterministic rare features, styles, and scales, creating endlessly redundant open architectures. 

Redundancy Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022
